<TEXT>
the sierra club said tuesday that it had 
supplied an incorrect airquality reading for providence ri in 
its report monday on smog problems across the nation 
dan weiss washington representative for the sierra club said 
the 1988 peak ozone reading for providence should have been 20 
parts per million not the 24 ppm contained in the list 
at a level of 24 ppm providence would have had the worst 
airquality reading among the 47 cities and counties covered in the 
list several cities and counties had readings that equaled or 
exceeded 20 ppm 
the federal health standard for ozone pollution is 12 ppm 
ozone which causes respiratory problems is formed when nitrogen 
oxides and hydrocarbons combine in the presence of sunlight 
