<TEXT>
urban chinese parents are pushing their children 
to learn too much too fast in their attempt to get the kids on the 
fast track according to studies reported in a newspaper 
the guangming daily said tuesday that if such a tendency 
continues china will soon be confronted with a family education 
crisis 
it said parents have stopped teaching their children values 
like morality and the joys of labor because they are spending too 
much time cramming their childrens heads with facts 
a study of 2294 elementary students in beijing indicatea the 
children help out in the house for an average of just 12 minutes a 
day the paper said american children help out for about 72 minutes 
every day 
another study in zhejiang province in central china found that 
more than 80 percent of families in one county do not make their 
elementary school age children to do any housework as long as their 
grades are good 
one teacher reported that in his class of 32 children 20 cant 
dress themselves and more than 10 have their feet and hair washed 
by their mothers 
the paper said a third study of children in shanghai ages 4 to 
6 found that 27 percent have psychiatric abnormalities linked to a 
poor family environment 
the guangming daily is a leading paper for intellectuals in 
china its report made reference only to children from urban areas 
where competition for access to the few good high schools and 
universities is most intense 
in the countryside where 75 percent of chinas 107 billion 
people live the opposite situation occurs peasants are often 
loathe to send their children to school because the youngsters can 
be put to work making money for the family 
the paper said parents should not turn their homes into a 
classroom for their children 
i parents see their childrens arent learning quickly enough 
and then get mad at them the children will lose all interest in 
studying even before they enter school the paper said 
in recent years the paper said the chinese press has been 
filled with reports about child prodigies 
here a 3yearold can memorize 100 tang dynasty poems there a 
5yearold can handle integral equations it said but in their 
goal to create an early genius many families dont take into 
account whether the child is interested or whether he has a 
superior intellect 
the paper cited the case of a 7yearold boy in liaoning 
province who cut off his fingers because he didnt want to practice 
piano 
these families dont realize it but theyve taken the golden 
years of childhood and turned them into bitter years for their 
children the paper said 
