<TEXT>
in a ceremony as old as their legislative 
body senators have sworn to do impartial justice in the 
impeachment trial of us district judge alcee l hastings but the 
trial wont happen until next year 
it was like a page of history tuesday as senators became judges 
and jurors in an impeachment case for only the 13th time in their 
history 
but the proceeding did more for history buffs than for advancing 
the impeachment case as senate majority leader robert byrd 
dwva announced that time constraints in the 100th congress will 
make a trial impossible until next year 
hastings who was not present at the senate session is the 
first defendant to be impeached after winning acquittal on similar 
charges at a criminal trial he also is the first black impeachment 
defendant 
the house formally presented 17 articles of impeachment along 
with its recommendation that the miami jurist be ousted for 
committing high crimes and misdemeanors 
language in the oath used to swear in senators and in a 
proclamation ordering them to keep silent on the pain of 
imprisonment was adopted for the first impeachment case in 
december 1798 
the senate at that time dismissed charges against sen william 
blount of tennessee saying a senator could not be impeached 
the house voted 4133 on aug 3 to impeach hastings accusing 
him of participating in a bribery conspiracy lying about the 
conspiracy at his criminal trial leaking confidential wiretap 
information and discrediting the federal judiciary 
impeachment is the way congress removes federal officials from 
office especially federal judges who are appointed for life after 
the house votes for impeachment akin to an indictment the senate 
conducts a trial in which conviction requires a twothirds majority 
of those present and voting 
senators approved a summons directing hastings to answer the 
impeachment articles by sept 8 
the rules committee was asked to report by sept 23 on whether 
the senate should use a committee to hear the evidence before the 
case is presented to the full chamber that system was used for the 
first time in the last impeachment trial which resulted in the 
conviction of harry e claiborne and his removal as a us district 
judge in las vegas nev 
the committee also is to report on the authority of the senate 
to receive impeachment articles in one congress and conduct a trial 
in another house precedents show it has been done twice before 
on tuesday house managers who function as prosecutors 
were led into the chamber by the house and senate sergeants at 
arms with chief manager peter w rodino jr dnj at the head 
