<TEXT>
here are highlights from the preliminary 
working papers that the republican platform committee is using 
to fashion the partys 1988 platform 
the seven issue papers totaling nearly 30000 words underwent 
revision by platform subcommittees tuesday before being sent to the 
full committee to be put in final form by friday 
the committee will present the final document to the republican 
national convention for approval tuesday 
here are excerpts 
america again leads the world confident of its abilities 
proud of its products sure of its future the pacesetter for all 
mankind now the ideological heirs of carter and mondale are 
trying again to sell the public a false bill of goods these 
luddite liberals call americas prosperity an illusion 
taxes we oppose any attempts to increase taxes 
republicans unequivocally reiterate the notax pledge we have 
proudly kept 
deficit we call for structural changes to control government 
waste including a twoyear budget cycle a supermajority 
requirement for raising taxes and a legislatively enacted 
lineitem veto we call for a balanced budget amendment to the 
constitution 
family calls for imparting to children the judeochristian 
values of western civilization and our ideals of liberty 
child care the best care for most children especially in the 
early years is parental government must never hinder it it 
promises to establish a toddler tax credit for preschool 
children available to all families of modest means 
aids those who suffer from aids their families and the men 
and women of medicine who care for the affliced deserve our 
compassion and help we will vigorously fight against aids 
we must not only marshal our scientific resources against aids but 
must also protect those who do not have the disease 
social security we pledge to preserve the integrity of the 
social security trust funds 
homeless republicans are determined to help the homeless as a 
matter of ethical commitment as well as sound public policy 
homelessness demonstrates the failure of liberalism it is the 
result of democratic policies in the 1960s and 1970s that disrupted 
mental health care family stability lowcost housing and the 
authority of towns and cities to deal with people in need 
promises to address root causes by strengthening enforcement of 
child support laws improving safety in shelters educating 
homeless children and breaking through red tape that keep 17 
million housing units unrehabilitated and out of use 
school prayer mindful of our religious diversity we firmly 
support the right of students to engage in voluntary prayer in 
schools also the pledge of allegiance should be recited daily 
in schools in all states 
abortion we believe the unborn child has a fundamental right 
to life which cannot be infringed we reaffirm our support for 
a human life amendment we oppose the use of public revenues 
for abortion we reaffirm our support for the appointment of 
judges at all levels of the judiciary who respect traditional 
family values and the sanctity of innocent human life 
women we renew our historic commitment to equal rights for 
women we must remove remaining obstacles to womens achieving 
their full potential and full reward that does not include the 
notion of federally mandated comparable worth 
ethics the founding fathers would be shocked by 
congressional behavior outright offenses against ethical 
standards and public laws are treated lightly we will apply 
health and safety laws and civil rights statutes to the congress 
education no students should be barred from a school or 
assigned to it because of race we will increase funding for 
the head start program we will keep the spotlight of public 
attention on the college cost spiral we will create a college 
savings bond program with taxexempt interest 
drugs opposes legalizing any illicit drug urges states to 
suspend eligibility for a drivers license to anyone convicted of a 
drug offense we will encourage tougher penalties for those who 
deal drugs near schools or use children to deliver narcotics 
to protect residents of public housing we will evict persons 
dealing in drugs it promises we will use our armed forces in 
the war on drugs to the maximum extent practical 
welfare work is an essential component of welfare reform 
energy calls for tax incentives to encourage exploration for 
new oil and to improve he recovery of oil still in place we 
support fully decontrolling natural gas prices supports 
expansion of environmentally safe nuclear power 
soviet relations americans cannot afford a future 
administration which attempts to eagerly embrace perceived but as 
yet unproven changes in soviet policy nor can we indulge naive 
inexperience or an overly enthusiastic endorsement of current 
soviet rhetoric we will not leave america unpepared should 
reform prove illusory 
anticommunism republicans proudly reaffirm the reagan 
doctrine americas commitment to aid freedom fighters against that 
which destroys freedom and the human spirit communist oppression 
nicaragua calls it a soviet client state that denies basic 
rights to its people today thousands of nicaraguans are united 
in a struggle to free their homeland from a totalitarian regime 
the republican party stands shoulder to shoulder with them in this 
struggle and is committed to assist them including military aid 
if necessary 
cuba opposes any normalization of relations as long as 
fidel castro continues to oppress the cuban people at home and 
support international terrorism and drug trafficking abroad 
taiwan we reaffirm our commitment to the security of 
taiwan of communist china it says as we draw closer in 
friendship the republican party believes that we must continue to 
encourage the abandonment of political repression in china and 
moves toward freer markets 
middle east republicans reject the concept of a palestinian 
state between jordan and israel such a state would pose a grave 
threat to the security interests of the united states and israel 
serving as a breeding ground for future radical and terrorist 
activities it says the plo should have no role in the peace 
process unless it recognizes israels right to exist 
apartheid republicans deplore the apartheid system of south 
africa republicans call for an effective and coordinated policy 
that will promote equal rights and a peaceful transition to a truly 
representative constitutional form of government for all south 
africa says actions designed to pressure the government of 
south africa must not have the effect of adversely affecting the 
rising aspirations and achievements of black south african 
entrepreneurs and workers 
strategic defense initiative sdi represents americas single 
most important defense program it is the most significant 
investment we can make in our nations future security we are 
commited to deployment of sdi as soon as possible 
arms talks arms reduction can be an important aspect of our 
national policy only when agreements enhance the security of the 
united states and its allies we will consistently undertake 
necessary improvements in our forces to maintain the credibility of 
our deterrent we will not negotiate in areas which jeopardize our 
security particularly sdi 
space the republican party will reestablish us 
preeminence in space we must commit to manned flight to mars 
around the year 2000 and to continued exploration of the moon 
</TEXT>
