<TEXT>
kurdish separatists are fighting a 
lastditch battle with iraqi troops who are using poison gas to 
drive them from their mountain stronghold in northeastern iraq a 
kurdish leader said 
the kurdish democratic party leader massoud barzani said 
tuesday that the iraqi offensive began july 30 he said about 
30000 iraqis were involved and have been backed by chemical 
weapons air raids and heavy artillery fire 
the statement received in nicosia from an athens office of the 
party appealed to the united nations and the world to stop the 
iraqis particularly now that the kurdish people are the target 
of gas attacks and face planned extermination 
it said the iraqi move was aimed at driving out the kurds before 
a un force assigned to monitor an aug 20 ceasefire in the 
iraniraq war arrives our guerrillas are putting up stiff 
resistance and have succeeded in preventing iraqis from achieving 
their main object of dislodging our fighters and arriving at 
international frontiers before the ceasefire is officially 
declared the kurds statement said 
throughout the 8year war iran has supported the autonomy 
movement of iraqs 35 million kurds and has sent arms and supplies 
across the border to them iran and turkey also have large kurdish 
populations 
the statement said the kurdish guerrillas are holding out in 
erbil province in the triangle of northeastern iraq that is 
bordered by turkey and iran 
according to irans official islamic republic news agency two 
villages near the town of shirwan in the turkish border region 
have been evacuated because of chemical attacks 
the kurds statement said 63 civilians were seriously injured in 
the latest gas attack it said kurdish refugees were fleeing to 
turkey and iran 
iran has given sanctuary to the kurds leaders including 
massoud barzani son of the legendary kurdish resistance leader 
the late mullah mustafa barzani 
the iranian news agency quoted a kurdish leader as saying the 
kurds would hold out as long as possible but would bring major 
parts of their forces to iran because of the iraq armys threats 
the kurdish statement said 1000 iraqi soldiers had been killed 
in the fighting the iranian news agency said iraq had deployed 12 
brigades and 18 light battalions against the kurds a total of 
15000 men 
about 20 million kurds are spread across an area covering parts 
of turkey iran iraq the soviet union and syria 
iraqi kurds have been fighting for autonomy for more than 50 
years 
