two royal air force tornado jet fighters collided 
during a night training flight over northwest england and the raf 
said today that three airman were killed and the fourth was missing 
and presumed dead 
the raf said in a statement that two bodies were found before 
dawn in wreckage strewn over the countryside near the village of 
