<TEXT>
here are excerpts from recent editorials in newspapers 
throughout the nation 
 
aug 4 
the westerly ri sun on disclosing unpublished information 
every now and then some court plays variations on the pernicious 
theme that reporters are obligated to help the police 
this has happened again in california where an appellate court 
ruled that a reporter and photographer had a duty to disclose their 
unpublished information about an arrest they witnessed 
taken at face value the judicial rationale may seem persuasive 
newspeople are as much obliged as anyone else to testify about what 
they witnessed in public 
but second thought suggests as a los angeles times lawyer 
noted that converting reporters into automatic witnesses would 
seriously weaken their rightful posture of objectivity 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
aug 3 
charleston wva daily mail on michael dukakis and foreign 
policy 
