american airlines today announced plans to base up 
to 700 pilots and flight attendants in southern florida home of 
embattled eastern airlines 
american based in fort worth texas is deeply committed to 
the florida market and believes florida will play a critical role 
in our future expansion said robert w baker senior vice 
president for operations 
american one of the industrys fastestgrowing large airlines 
also announced it will add a flight attendant crew base in 
nashville tenn the miami and nashville sites bring americans 
total crew bases to 12 
by january american will base 160 flight crew members in miami 
fort lauderdale and west palm beach baker said the total will 
reach 700 within a few years he said 
baker said several hundred american employees already live in 
south florida 
american officials said that the move will help in expanding 
service to the caribbean that began with establishment of a hub in 
san juan puerto rico but that it was too early to estimate the 
number of new flights that could be added 
american over the past two years increased its daily flights in 
florida from 29 to 78 and boarded nearly 1 million passengers in 
florida in the first six months of 1988 compared to 412000 the 
first half of 1986 
americans growth comes as miamibased eastern airlines is 
cutting back and could put american in position to capitalize on 
the problems of eastern and pan american world airways 
eastern and pan am the two most active carriers at miami 
international airport are seeking major labor cutbacks and there 
has been speculation they are considering selling off their 
lucrative south american routes 
baker said americans expansion to southern florida is based on 
longterm plans not on competitors possibly temporary problems 
i dont think it will have any effect eastern spokeswoman 
paual musto said american is in a growing mode and if miami is 
their choice i say more power to the miami community and economy 
eastern with its corporate headquarters here has some 850 
pilots and 1800 flight attendants based in miami she said 
texas air corp on monday announced it lost 2559 million in 
the second quarter with operating losses at both its major 
carriers eastern and continental airlines 
americans new flight attendant crew base in nashville will have 
75 flight attendants in october and perhaps as many as 600 in the 
early 1990s the airline said 
