a white foster mother drew five years in 
prison for the dehydration death of a foster baby who prosecutors 
said was neglected because he was black 
judith lundy was convicted in june of murder and manslaughter in 
the 1985 death of 4monthold corey greer the 50yearold woman 
tuesday told judge susan schaeffer i take full responsibility 
mrs lundy allowed the infant to die in a steamy urinesoaked 
room because touching a black baby gave her the willies 
according to testimony at her trial 
at the time of the babys death mrs lundy was caring for 12 
foster children and her own daughter she was licensed by the state 
to care for only four children 
in the aftermath state officials admitted failing to ensure 
that foster children were placed in clean uncrowded foster homes 
thirteen employees of the health and rehabilitative service 
department were disciplined 
the judge agreed tuesday that the state child care agency had 
been negligent in placing so many children in mrs lundys care but 
said the department was not on trial 
prosecutors said mrs lundy allowed an 8yearold foster child 
to tend the baby the 8yearold testified she told mrs lundy that 
corey seemed sick the night before he died 
