bolts 35 inches in diameter and 28 inches long during a launch 
the nuts to those bolts would be exploded apart to release the ship 
the engines built up to 11 million pounds of thrust in the 
first 66 seconds the energy output of 23 hoover dams and a 
thunderclap rolled across the launch site 
