<TEXT>
american and soviet scientists 
looking for solutions to global pollution are cruising portions of 
the bering sea that long have been offlimits to us scientists 
the sixweek joint research project is the third expedition in 
the last 10 years similar studies in 1979 and in 1984 were 
restricted at soviet insistence to us waters 
this will enable us to fill in a lot of the gaps in our data 
about how the ocean operates on the soviet side said john 
goering an organizer of the us research team before now 
weve had to guess at how the currents and dynamics of that part of 
the bering sea work 
most of the soviet scientists are monitoring pollution levels 
and determining how pollutants are transported in the bering and 
chukchi seas 
alla tsiban the chief soviet scientist on the cruise was a 
member of the 1984 expedition that found trace amounts of toxic 
pcbs in the bering sea 
in my opinion most of it comes from the atmosphere she 
said i expect we will find higher levels this time we will 
combine our efforts this expedition to determine the load capacity 
of the marine ecosystem for these pollutants 
pat roscigno a us fish and wildlife service scientist said 
researchers can figure out how to control the pollution if they can 
determine where its coming from and how much is in the water 
