<TEXT>
govs mario cuomo and thomas kean reacting to 
the beach pollution which has marred the summer in their states 
said wednesday a cradletograve accounting of all infectious 
medical waste was now required in new york and new jersey 
the purpose is to say to people we will watch you with the 
intent of catching and prosecuting you if this waste is not 
disposed of properly new yorks cuomo told a crowded shipboard 
news conference in new york harbor 
kean speaking with the statue of liberty in the background 
agreed we will no longer tolerate the careless unsupervised and 
often just outrageous way these wastes are being handled 
the plan was announced following a monthlong rash of beach 
closings in both states due to medical waste and raw sewage in the 
water syringes blood vials bandages and other infectious waste 
have washed ashore in new jersey and new york beaches in new york 
also had dead rats on the sand 
beach attendance has been down significantly in both states 
because of the washedup waste officials have said 
the problem has cropped up elsewhere too 
syringes vials of drugs and other medical debris have washed 
ashore from the gulf of mexico onto beaches in floridas panhandle 
during the past several weeks authorities there said wednesday 
but one official escambia county environmental health director 
richard dunlap said there was no cause for alarm from a health 
standpoint 
its medical waste its not infectious waste he said 
the storm has brought in so much stuff in addition to medical 
debris tropical storm beryl churned up the gulf earlier this 
week before dissipating 
twentysix miles of north carolina beaches were soiled by waste 
dumped by offshore navy vessels and since sunday marines have 
been working to clean up the sand 
navy regulations allow dumping of biodegradable garbage within 
12 miles of shore said lt cmdr john lloyd a navy spokesman 
other trash may be dumped 25 miles or more from shore but medical 
refuse that may be contaminated or connected with dangerous drugs 
is held for incineration in port he said 
its not a contamination problem and i can say its 
definitely not related to the beach problems in new york and new 
jersey lloyd said 
as part of the new yorknew jersey plan any facility which 
generates medical waste any company which transports it and any 
place which disposes of it will be required to fill out forms at 
each step of the process 
the hospital will then keep the final form completed at all 
three stops on file for the state providing a record of the 
waste from inception to disposal if the hospital does not receive 
the form within seven days of disposal the state must be notified 
the plan went into effect immediately in both new york and new 
jersey the governors said 
we are powerless no longer as needles and bandages wash up on 
our beaches said kean we will be able to punish the people 
who have been turning so many holidays into horror stories 
but both cuomo and kean acknowledged the new manifest system 
did not carry any stricter penalties for illegal dumpers it 
simply would make it easier to catch them 
and both governors used the occasion to call for tougher fines 
and possible jail terms against violators kean also reiterated his 
request for creation of a new jersey coastal commission to monitor 
the states beachfronts 
the gubernatorial gettogether came one day after the us 
environmental protection agency said it had no plans to regulate 
medical waste disposal kean and cuomo disagreed with that 
we want federal legislation only when its needed and here it 
is needed cuomo said 
