vehicles started in heavy rain at low tide wednesday afternoon 
levine said he was pleased with the militarys response they 
have conceded their responsibilities he said they will clean 
up the entire situation no matter how long it takes and dispose 
of the waste properly 
it is not clear if north carolina statutes outlaw such dumping 
lt gov bob jordan said at a news conference in raleigh he has 
requested an opinion from the state attorney general on the law 
covering such situations proposing a law to prohibit dumping of 
waste into the ocean if the attorney general rules it is not 
covered by current law 
