south china sea crossing which began may 22 when the group left 
the mekong delta town of ben tre aboard a 35foot wooden boat 
its engine failed two or three days later 
according to the navy the dubuque on its way to the persian 
gulf encountered the vietnamese vessel on june 9 
the craft was judged to be in seaworthy condition and was 
under sail the navy said in a statement issued tuesday 
the uss dubuque gave the refugees food water and navigational 
charts before resuming transit to the indian ocean 
cooper said the refugees are claiming that by june 9 there 
was one dead refugee aboard the motor was not working they were 
drifting for 19 days people had died of exposure hunger and 
thirst 
