bills requirement for a commission to develop minimum health 
safety and training standards that would be mandatory for those day 
care homes and centers accepting the federal aid 
as introduced the abc bill would have allowed federal funds to 
churchbased day care centers only if they did not promote religion 
in any way they would have had to comply with federal bans on 
religious discrimination in hiring and admissions 
