<TEXT>
bank of new england corp a holding company 
based in boston was granted permission by the federal reserve 
board on wednesday to offer investment advice to both retail and 
institutional customers 
the board said the company can offer the service through a 
subsidiary new england discount brokerage inc which already 
provides brokerage services 
the fed in its order noted that it has previously authorized 
bank holding companies to offer investment advice in conjunction 
with brokerage services to institutional customers but it never 
before permitted the combination with retail customers 
the order forbids new england discount brokerage from trading 
for its own account in any of the securities that it recommends it 
also provides that the board of directors of the brokerage must be 
separate from the board of the parent holding company 
bank of new england corp with 288 billion in assets is the 
19th largest bank holding company in the nation it operates 
subsidiary banks in massachussets connecticut maine and rhode 
island 
</TEXT>
