<TEXT>
some remember with flowers on a grassy rise by an 
interstate highway overpass others remember with prayers for the 
156 people lost in the crash of northwest airlines flight 255 
around the country a year after the plane plowed into 
middlebelt road on a drizzly sunday evening many remember the 
cherubic face of little cecelia cichan 
cecelia then 4 years old was the only passenger to survive the 
aug 16 1987 crash her mother father and brother were among the 
victims she lives with an aunt and uncle in birmingham ala who 
have a legal agreement to protect cecelia in hopes she can lead as 
normal a life as possible they turn down interview requests 
but other people relatives rescuers and investigators have 
found that talking about the tragedy helps 
less than a minute after the elongated twinengine dc9s front 
wheels left runway 3center at detroit metropolitan airport bound 
for phoenix ariz one wing clipped a parking lot light pole 41 
feet high 
as the jet banked toward a car rental agency part of the other 
wing was sheared off a subsequent investigation determined the 
pilots had failed to extend the planes wing flaps to provide lift 
on takeoff 
flight 255 slammed into a fourlane road and broke apart as it 
skidded under railroad and interstate 94 overpasses killing two 
people on the ground and everyone aboard except cecelia shielded 
from catastrophe by a womans body 
the toll made it the nations seconddeadliest air disaster the 
crash of an american airlines dc10 in chicago on may 25 1979 
chicago killed 275 people 
broken bodies and burning chunks of the northwest wreckage were 
strewn for thousands of feet along middlebelt road and on the 
detroitchicago interstate 
lawrence favio an airport baggage handler was driving home for 
a dinner break at 846 pm when a sheet of flaming metal smashed 
into his thunderbird weeks later he and cecelia met at burn unit 
in the university of michigan medical center 
today he remembers the crash every time he looks at the 
mummylike wrappings that cover his hands and extend to his elbows 
betty polec of mount clemens remembers too her daughter and 
soninlaw were among the victims 
in december polec and others held the first meeting of flight 
255 their spirit lives on a support group with about 85 members 
the people who have joined the group we have formed a 
bond she said weve worn each others shoes 
other relatives of victims needed to deal with the crash in 
different ways 
ive had some people tell me on the telephone i dont want 
anything to do with this group just remember my loved one 
polec said and we do 
on tuesdays anniversary of the crash polecs group plans a 
vigil on middlebelt road where flowers have been placed since the 
plane went down a light will be lit as each of the victims names 
is read polec said 
law officers remember too 
some have sought psychological help three percent to 7 percent 
have developed significant posttraumatic disorders said 
psychologist kenneth wolf who counseled rescuers on the night of 
the crash 
some deputies today still dont want to drive down middlebelt 
because it brings back many memories of the night of the crash 
wolf said 
other deputies are looking for a man with a gray beard who 
showed up the day after the crash and began consoling victims 
families claiming to be a roman catholic priest father john 
irish 
some families became suspicious when he referred them to a 
florida attorney but by that time irish had vanished an arrest 
warrant alleged he defrauded northwest out of motel and meal costs 
and wayne county sheriff robert ficano said irish was suspected of 
similar activity at other tragedies 
but many others tried to brighten the lives darkened by 
disaster for the 68 days cecelia was in the ann arbor hospital 
americans opened their hearts and pocketbooks spokesman michael 
harrison said the hospital received 157420 in cash and checks 
all deposited in a trust fund more than 30000 cards and letters 
and 2200 gifts mostly stuffed animals 
cecelias family gave most of the gifts to childrens hospitals 
in michigan phoenix and the philadelphia area where cecelias 
grandparents live harrison said 
the pain and suffering has also been relived in a federal 
courtroom and a motel conference room 
attorneys from at least four states have filed 105 lawsuits 
naming northwest for pretrial purposes all the suits have been 
consolidated in federal court in detroit 
the next hearing is set for september district court executive 
john mayer said it wasnt clear which suits would be tried or where 
in november the national transportation safety board held a 
weeklong public hearing at a motel less than a mile from the crash 
site on may 10 the board found that the two pilots had failed to 
properly set the airplanes flaps an alarm to alert them to their 
error failed to sound according to cockpit tapes but it has not 
been determined whether it malfunctioned or was deliberately shut 
off 
if the flaps had been extended normally at the time of the 
crash investigators said the plane which never got more than 50 
feet off the ground would have been about 600 feet in the air 
climbing toward cruising altitude on its way to phoenix 
</TEXT>
