its controversial collar which bans the use of the exchanges 
computer system for index arbitrage on days when the dow average 
rises or falls 50 points from the previous close 
this marks the sixth time the collar has been put into effect 
since it was approved as a temporary measure in april the 
securities and exchange commission is reviewing reforms that 
include coordinated trading halts when the dow falls 250 points 
