<TEXT>
bond prices tumbled wednesday in active trading 
still reeling from the shock of tuesdays increase in the discount 
rate and catapulting interest rates to their highest levels this 
year 
the treasurys closely watched 30year bond dropped about 1 
points or a hefty 1750 for every 1000 in face value its 
yield which moves inversely to its price and is often an indicator 
of interest rate trends surged to 936 percent from 919 percent 
late tuesday 
the yield on the key 30year issue hasnt been that high since 
dec 10 1987 when it reached 940 percent 
shortterm treasury bills were mixed 
analysts said bond prices continued to be weakened by the 
halfpoint rise to 65 percent in the interest rate the federal 
reserve charges on loans to member us financial institutions 
the markets slashing its wrists again said ward mccarthy 
chief financial economist at merrill lynch capital markets 
many bond traders are fearful that tuesdays move could be the 
first of a series of hikes in the discount rate analysts say 
the fed said it raised the discount rate to reduce inflationary 
pressures on the economy 
credit markets are concerned that increased inflation could 
erode the value of fixedincome securities such as bonds a rise in 
interest rates however tends to send bond prices lower 
analysts said bonds were also dragged down by market 
expectations that a government auction of 11 billion in 10year 
treasury notes late wednesday wouldnt be well received by 
investors on tuesday the governments companion auction of 
threeyear notes had been disappointing 
the negative expectations for wednesdays note sale were 
confirmed late in the trading session when the results were 
announced by the treasury 
